Comments: Co-chaperone, nucleotide exchange factor for Hsp70

Name: GRPEL2
Comments: Co-chaperone, nucleotide exchange factor for Hsp70

Name: DNAJB2
Comments: Neuronal DnaJ/Hsp40 chaperone, suppresses protein aggregation

Name: DNAJB6
Comments: Restores mitophagy by promoting protein relocation

Name: CRYAB
Comments: HSPB5. Has chaperone-like activity, preventing aggregation of various proteins under a wide range of stress conditions. I

Name: CLPX
Comments: ATP-dependent chaperone that functions as an unfoldase.

Name: HSCB
Comments: DNAJC20; Mitochondrial Iron-Sulfur Cluster Cochaperonem important for SDHB

Name: SDHAF1
Comments: Co-chaperone of HSCB. The succinate dehydrogenase (SDH) complex (or complex II) of the mitochondrial respiratory chain is composed of 4 individual subunits. The protein encoded by this gene resides in the mitochondria, and is essential for SDH assembly, but does not physically associate with the complex in vivo. Mutations in this gene are associated with SDH-defective infantile leukoencephalopathy
